data.chText: 开始从事，发起，发动（尤指有组织的活动）
data.enText: to start an activity, especially an organized one

data.chText: 开始进行上诉 / 质询 / 调查 / 一场运动
data.enText: to launch an appeal/an inquiry/an investigation/a campaign

data.chText: 发起攻击；发动侵略
data.enText: to launch an attack/invasion

data.chText: （首次）上市，发行
data.enText: to make a product available to the public for the first time

data.chText: 他最新小说的首发式
data.enText: a party to launch his latest novel

data.chText: 新型号产品将在七月推出。
data.enText: The new model will be launched in July.

data.chText: 使（船，尤指新船）下水
data.enText: to put a ship or boat into the water, especially one that has just been built

data.chText: 海军今天有一艘新军舰要下水。
data.enText: The Navy is to launch a new warship today.

data.chText: 那艘救生艇被立刻放下了水。
data.enText: The lifeboat was launched immediately.

data.chText: 发射；把（航天器、武器等）发射上天；水中发射
data.enText: to send sth such as a spacecraft , weapon, etc. into space, into the sky or through water

data.chText: 发射通信卫星
data.enText: to launch a communications satellite

data.chText: 发射导弹 / 火箭 / 鱼雷
data.enText: to launch a missile/rocket/torpedo

data.chText: 猛扑向前
data.enText: to jump forwards with a lot of force

data.chText: 他突然向我猛扑过来。
data.enText: Without warning he launched himself at me.
launch into sth
launch yourself into sth

data.chText: （热情地）开始做，投入
data.enText: to begin sth in an enthusiastic way, especially sth that will take a long time

data.chText: 他开始啰啰唆唆地讲述自己的工作经历。
data.enText: He launched into a lengthy account of his career.
launch out

data.chText: 开始从事，投身于（新的、尤指更令人兴奋的事业）
data.enText: to do sth new in your career, especially sth more exciting

data.chText: 该是我自己创业的时候了。
data.enText: It's time I launched out on my own.

data.chText: （航天器的）发射；（船的）下水；（产品的）上市；（事件的）发起

tr: the act of propelling with force
a motorboat with an open deck or a half deck

example: He launched into a long diatribe
She plunged into a dangerous adventure
Her actions set in motion a complicated judicial process
She set up a literacy program

value.def: To launch a rocket, missile, or satellite means to send it into the air or into space.

example.ex: NASA plans to launch a satellite to study cosmic rays...
example.tran: 美国国家航空航天局计划发射一颗卫星上天，对宇宙射线进行研究。

example.ex: A Delta II rocket was launched from Cape Canaveral early this morning.
example.tran: 今天一早，一枚“德尔塔”Ⅱ型火箭在卡纳维拉尔角发射升空。

example.ex: This morning's  launch of the space shuttle Columbia has been delayed.
example.tran: 原定今早“哥伦比亚”号航天飞机的发射已被推迟。

value.def: To launch a ship or a boat means to put it into water, often for the first time after it has been built.

example.ex: There was no time to launch the lifeboats because the ferry capsized with such alarming speed.
example.tran: 渡轮瞬间倾覆，根本没时间放救生艇下水。

example.ex: The launch of a ship was a big occasion.

value.tran: 使（船）下水；使（新船）首次下水

value.def: To launch a large and important activity, for example a military attack, means to start it.

example.ex: Heavy fighting has been going on after the guerrillas had launched their offensive...
example.tran: 游击队发起攻击后，激烈的战斗一直持续不断。

example.ex: The police have launched an investigation into the incident...
example.tran: 警方已对该事件展开调查。

example.ex: The President was on holiday when the coup was launched.
example.tran: 政变发动时，总统正在度假。

example.ex: ...the launch of a campaign to restore law and order.
example.tran: 发起一场旨在恢复法律和秩序的运动

value.tran: 开展（重大活动）；发起，发动（军事袭击等）

value.def: If a company launches a new product, it makes it available to the public.

example.ex: Crabtree & Evelyn has just launched a new jam, Worcesterberry Preserve...
example.tran: 瑰珀翠刚推出一款新果酱——伍斯特浆果果酱。

example.ex: Marks & Spencer recently hired model Linda Evangelista to launch its new range.
example.tran: 玛莎百货最近聘请模特儿琳达·埃万杰利斯塔为其发布新系列产品。

example.ex: The company's spending has also risen following the launch of a new Sunday magazine.
example.tran: 发行一本新周日杂志后，公司的开支也跟着上升。

value.def: A launch is a large motorboat that is used for carrying people on rivers and lakes and in harbours.

example.ex: The captain was on the deck of the launch, steadying the boat for the pilot...
example.tran: 船长站在汽艇甲板上为领航员保向。

example.ex: We'll make a trip by launch to White Island.
example.tran: 我们将乘汽艇到怀特岛。

value.tran: （在江河、湖泊和港口载人的）大型汽艇
